Churro Ice Cream Sandwiches
  --Chelsea's Messy Apron

Churros:
1/2 c whole milk
1/2 c water
pinch of salt
1 tbsp sugar
1/4 c (4 tbsp) unsalted butter
1 tsp vanilla
1 c white flour

In a saucepan over medium high heat, combine the milk, water, salt, sugar, and butter. Mix until the butter is melted and bring the mixture to a boil. As soon as it boils, remove from the heat and stir in the vanilla. Stir in the flour using a rubber spatula, continue to mix and press out any lumps, until the dough is completely smooth. Transfer the mixture to a large piping bag fitted with an open star tip. Onto a sheet of parchment paper, pipe long strips of dough. Allo to rest for 15-20 min. In the meantime, preheat deep fryer to 360F/ Carefully roll up strips of dough into a circle the size you want the sandwich to be. Place 2 churros at a time in the fryer. Fry until golden brown, flipping about halfway through cooking time (total time ~5-7 min). Remove and place onto a plate lined with paper towels.

Topping:
2 tbsp sugar
2 tbsp brown sugar
1 tsp cinnamon

Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Place the hot churros into the mixture and coat evenly. 

Assembly
ice cream

While still very warm, fill the center of a churro with ice cream and top with another. Enjoy immediately. Or....

Chocolate Ganache (optional)
1/4 c heavy whipping cream
1/4 c dark chocolate

Microwave cream in a bowl for 45 s - 1 m or until very hot. Pour in the chocolate chips and stir until smooth and creamy. Dunk the sandwich into the ganache as desired.
